      "id": "LN_02",
      "section": "learn",
      "difficulty": 0,
      "type": "concept_card",
      "title": "Strategy: Subtract from ×10",
      "content": "9 times a number = 10 times that number minus the number. 9 × 6 = 10 × 6 − 6 = 60 − 6 = 54.",
      "cpa_phase": "concrete",
      "visual_type": "none"
    },
    {
      "id": "LN_03",
      "section": "learn",
      "difficulty": 0,
      "type": "concept_card",
      "title": "Digit Sum Pattern",
      "content": "The digits of every ×9 product add up to 9: 9→9, 18→1+8=9, 27→2+7=9, 36→3+6=9, 45→4+5=9. Use it to check your answer.",
      "cpa_phase": "pictorial",
      "visual_type": "none"
    },
    {
      "id": "LN_04",
      "section": "learn",
      "difficulty": 0,
      "type": "concept_card",
      "title": "Two-Digit Rule for 9 × n",
      "content": "For 9 × n (where n is 1–10): tens digit = n − 1, ones digit = 10 − n. Example: 9 × 7 → tens = 6, ones = 3 → 63. Always check with the digit sum (6 + 3 = 9).",
      "cpa_phase": "pictorial",
      "visual_type": "none"
    },
