      "section": "learn",
      "difficulty": 0,
      "type": "concept_card",
      "title": "Finger Trick for 9s",
      "content": "Hold up 10 fingers. To find 9 × n, fold down the n-th finger. Fingers LEFT of it = tens digit; fingers RIGHT of it = ones digit. Example: 9 × 4 — fold 4th finger: 3 fingers left, 6 fingers right → 36.",
